Laikipia became the first Mt Kenya county to pass the Constitution of Kenya (Amendment), Bill 2020 on Thursday. This brings to nine, the counties whivh have passed the Bill. Other counties that have passed the Bill are Kisii, Siaya, Kisumu, Kajiado, West Pokot, Busia, Trans Nzoia and Homa Bay. So far, only Baringo County has rejected the Bill. Twenty-four out of 47 counties are required to pass the Bill